Catacomb entry clearance
-1 1 3 0 8 22 3063 1200 3 13000 0
21000 21001 21002
Midgaard's dispatch couriers have stopped running eastern gate routes because the catacomb approaches beneath the city have become infested with vermin. The Crossroads Dispatch office needs the upper tunnel approaches cleared: eliminate one ash tunnel rat, one ledger mite, and one candle scavenger to restore safe passage through the entry corridors. Gate manifest deliveries depend on those routes staying open.
The upper catacomb approaches are clear enough for courier runs to resume. Dispatch confirmations are moving to the eastern gate again, and the route backlog has started to drain. The Ledgerhouse has updated the approach hazard rating from impassable to manageable, and the city messenger corps has reopened the route to standard single-runner schedules.
